      "text": "# Midcontinent Independent System Operator (MISO)\n\nMidcontinent Independent System Operator (MISO) is a Utilities company. Midcontinent Independent System Operator (MISO) is a company that provides services related to market monitoring, market system enhancement, market reports, registration, reliability information, winterization, settlements, notifications, and transmission planning. Midcontinent Independent System Operator (MISO) employs 872 people (+3.9% YoY, +50 people) and has an annual revenue of $420.0M, founded in 2001. Headquartered in Carmel, Indiana, United States, with presence in France and India.\n\n## About\nMISO is the electric grid operator for the central United States. The organization ensures power flows reliably and affordably to more than 45 million people across 15 states and the Canadian province of Manitoba. Additionally, MISO facilitates the buying and selling of electricity in its region and assists with planning the grid of the future.\n\n## Company Details\n- In",
